Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo
TOKYO , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Stock prices fell in Tokyo on Monday with the key Nikkei index closing below 15,000 for the first time in a week as skepticism over an alliance between the Liberal Democratic Party ( LDP ) and Liberal Party ( LP ) thickened .
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 185.69 points , or 1.23 percent , from last Friday 's close to end at 14 , 883.70 .
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index ( TOPIX ) , covering all First Section issues , dropped 14.85 points or 1.28 percent to 1 , 143.50 .
Turnover on the major section slid to an estimated 382 million shares from Friday 's 506.20 million shares .
Sakura Bank was the day 's most heavily traded issue .
Selling accelerated in the afternoon when Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi told the Diet ( parliament ) it would be " difficult " to reduce or suspend the 5 percent consumption tax , something LP lawmakers want to encourage personal spending .
It looks like some investors have lost hope on a sales tax cut , and this is having a psychological impact on the market , a dealer said .
Skepticism over the LDP-LP alliance itself thickened when Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiromu Nonaka hinted the tie-up may not necessarily lead to an immediate reshuffling of the cabinet , traders said .
